Rating: 3
This was great! I gave it 3 forks because of the thin sauce. I would make a few changes in the future, but I am definitely making this again, for company! First, I would bake the apples separately with more spices, like cinnamon. (if you had a problem with the sauce thickening, it is because the apples add too much water to the sauce, and you have to reduce it forever) Then I would make the cream sauce with the applejack, wine and spices. I'll also broil a pork loin instead of chops. (I'll let you know how it turns out) I served this with Brussels Sprouts roasted with garlic and herbs de provence; they made a nice savory compliment to the sweetness of the main course. And a crusty baguette. My husband loved it.

