Rating: 4
I love this combination of pork chops, apple and white wine; the flavors are a true compliment to one another. It is possible to make a scaled down version, that is also exceptionaly delicious. Brown chops sprinkled with seasoned salt, instead of celery salt. After browning, remove chops, add 1 medium chopped onion & 1 more Tab. butter, add chops back to pan and continue. The apple jack or Calvados is really a glorified option, just increase white wine to 1/2 cup. Heavy cream can also be omitted, if you are watching calories; but make them both ways and see if there is a difference. Most important, just enjoy.